	<TD WIDTH="20%"><FONT FACE="arial" SIZE="2" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Author</FONT></TD>
	<TD><FONT FACE="arial" SIZE="2"COLOR="#FFFFFF">Character 'Distinctiveness'</FONT></TD>
</TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#333333" ALIGN="LEFT">
<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="arial" COLOR="#FFFFFF"><b>Strumm</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="arial" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B></B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="arial" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Joined: Apr 30, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="arial" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Posts: 46</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="arial" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF">From: Wales (GMT)<br></FONT></td><TD><img src="/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="arial" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Posted: 2001-05-01 16:58&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF" face="arial">I've heard quite a bit about GLs unique ideas on making individual characters distinct from one another, but I wonder how far they'll let us take it.<BR><BR>I'm pretty sure one of the HoC mentioned that wounds will leave scars (which let's face it is pretty cool), but will it be possible to permanently lose a hand or a leg for example?<BR><BR>Also, we've heard about tatoos and such involving dyes, but will it be possible to use similar dyes to change the colour of a characters hair or even skin (a la Celtic Woad Warriors)? Will it be possible to be bald or to grow a 'fro even?<BR><BR>And what about beards and stuff. Will characters grow facial hair over time, and if they do, will we be able to shave it and shape it (and dye it)? I'm not thinking ZZ Top here, just something to get my food caught up in.<BR><BR>And then there's the fat thing. We've been told that eating too little will eventually leave us too weak to function, but what if we eat too much? Will we get fat? Will that matter? Will individuals in communities with plenty of food grow to be faster and stronger than those who don't?<BR><BR>I mean if it's possible for two humans (say) to be as different as Meatloaf and Neal Peart (drummer from Rush), that could be quite cool.
<BR>_________________<BR></FONT><BR>
