<FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF" face="arial">The simple answer to all of your questions: No.<BR><BR>Unless GL adds in &quot;Persistent Model Changing&quot; the look of your chair will only be changed by pre-defined scar locales. That in itself is alot of work. <IMG SRC="/images/smiles/icon_frown.gif"><BR><BR>They would have to skin and model thousands of looks to be able to do what you ask. It's a <!-- BBCode Start --><I>grand</I><!-- BBCode End --> idea. But <!-- BBCode Start --><I>very</I><!-- BBCode End --> time consuming. <IMG SRC="/images/smiles/icon_frown.gif"><BR><BR>But it would be nice to hear some people's &quot;look&quot; idea's. I mean, it doesn't hurt to imagine what you could look like. <IMG SRC="/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif"><BR><BR><font size=-1>[ This Message was edited by: Tilwin Soulfire on 2001-05-04 15:43 ]</font></FONT><BR>
